item.title: About Our Founders
item.dc:creator: ahab
item.content:encoded:
Wes and Judy Pierce, originally from Illinois, were married in April of 1987. Their journey from child rearing to becoming proud grandparents, led them to Texas in 2001. After having five of their own sons serve in the military, Wes and Judy became increasingly aware of the unmet needs of our returning Veterans. Through their own children’s difficulties with accessing and finding resources and a very special SSGT Clark, Heroes Night Out was born.
Though much different in the beginning stages, Wes and Judy’s initial efforts were geared toward providing appreciation wallets containing gift cards to wounded soldiers so they could spend a little quality with their families.
Today, this ideology has expanded into a full service resource center. Heroes Night Out Veterans Resource Center offers easy access to much needed services. Veterans can get assistance with their VA claims, access legal support when appropriate, access employers, and so much more, all while spending time in the company of their Peers.
Wes and Judy have created family friendly events, which are free to Veterans and their families. These no cost events are the heart of the organization. This is where Veterans may come for the first time to get a feel for the organization and begin connecting with other Heroes.
The connection is key. When Vietnam Veterans begin connecting with today’s soldiers who are encountering some of the exact same struggles they had when returning from war, it is an amazing thing to experience. We have all seen so much healing in this place.
Wes and Judy invite you to come and enjoy dinner, completely free, and get to know more about how we can help you and how you may be able to help others.

item.title: Our On-Site Services
item.dc:creator: ahab
item.content:encoded:
Heroes Night Out Veterans Resource provides multiple on-site services in our 6,000 sq. foot facility in Austin TX. Resource Center Hours: Monday – Friday 9:00am – 4:00pm
  • VA Claims Specialist - Valerie Zimmerman, Williamson County Assistant Veterans Service Officer, in office on Tuesdays and Thursdays
  • VA Compensation and Pension Exams - Dr. Shirin Bazaz
  • Caregiver’s Corner - Every 4th Tuesday of each month at 7:00p PM (Dedicated to those who care for a disabled Veteran)
  • Vet Center Counselor - Dr. Elwanda Hawthorne, (Wednesdays, 1:00pm – 4:00 PM, by appointment only)
  • Military Veteran Peer Network - Tim Keesling, (Monday through Friday)
  • Veteran Home Loan Specialist - George Lourigan, Thursday mornings
  • University of Phoenix - Jim Johnson, Thursday mornings
  • Life Coaching - Ed Donovan, Thursdays, by appointment only
  • Computer Center with Internet and printing Monday – Friday 9:00am – 4:00pm
Family Room During holidays, Heroes Night Out makes sure Veterans and their families have meals, Christmas gifts, and other holiday support. It is our goal to provide a military friendly environment, with volunteers and staff who understand the hardships our Heroes face.  Our center offers a laid-back environment where Veterans can access many resources and connect with their Peers over a hot cup of coffee.

item.dc:creator: wpengine

This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:
Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)
...or something like this:
The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.

item.title: Heroes Night Out Mission statement
item.dc:creator: SecretSimple
item.content:encoded: What began as one couple’s mission to provide wounded Heroes with an appreciation wallet containing gift cards, has grown into a full service Veteran’s Resource Center. Heroes Night Out strives to connect our Veterans and their families with the resources and benefits available to them through local, state, and federal agencies. Heroes Night Out Veterans Resource Center is much more than a traditional drop-in center. We offer Peer to Peer events and activities that provide Veterans with the opportunity to connect and support one another through their shared Military experiences. More than anything else, our Veterans and Wounded Heroes are in need of a place with people that embrace them, support them, and encourage their continued success. Our resource center is fully equipped with a Veterans Claims Specialist, a VA Home Loan Consultant, Counselors, Military Veteran Peer to Peer specialists, and other convenient Veteran-friendly services.  ”Please know that I will always be grateful for you, Judy, Paul, Bob, and Mike! You all helped me get out of a very dark and scary place! You also gave me confidence and and a sense of purpose again! Thank you for caring about my kids as well as Nicole and I! Thanks so much for saving my life!” – Wounded Veteran – Iraq

item.title: Howto: Add New Event
item.dc:creator: ahab
item.content:encoded: After logging into word press as an editor or admin go to Events -> Add New: This will bring up the New Event creation page. On this page the required fields are highlighted in green: These fields are self-explanatory or mandatory. Of note: The Excerpt field will be a short description of the event that shows up in list view. The Tickets field will be for events with limited seating (Thanksgiving and dinners, but not Coffee and Peer to Peers). Once all  information has been entered hit the Publish button to publish the event.

item.title: Howto: Add News Post
item.dc:creator: ahab
item.content:encoded: After logging into word press as an editor or admin go to Events -> Add New: The highlighted fields are required for a full featured post: Once all information is entered "Publish" will make the post appear on the front page.

item.title: Ask For Help!
item.dc:creator: ahab
item.content:encoded:
If you require immediate assistance please contact 911. Vet Center Combat Call Center: 1-877-WAR-VETS is an around the clock confidential call center where combat Veterans and their families can call to talk about their military experience or any other issue they are facing in their readjustment to civilian life. The staff is comprised of combat Veterans from several eras as well as families members of combat Veterans. This benefit is prepaid through the Veteran’s military service. For help with critical issues Heroes Night Out offers the following services:
  • Vet Center Counselor – Dr. Elwanda Hawthorne, (Wednesdays, 1:00pm – 4:00 PM, by appointment only)
  • Military Veteran Peer Network – Tim Keesling, (Monday through Friday)
  • Life Coaching – Ed Donovan, Thursdays, by appointment only
If it is a non-emergency contact us and may be able to help with our additional on site services or attend one of our events.
